    Analyte Object

    Analyte.Rd

    Analyte class is an object that gathers information about one specific Analyte on the Luminex plate

    Public fields

    id

    A numeric value that represents the unique identifier of the analyte

    analyte_name

    A character value that represents the name of the analyte

    bead_count

    ? not exactly sure what this field means tbh

    analysis_type

    Type of the analyte

    units

    Units of the analyte in which the results are expressed

    Methods

    Public methods

    • Analyte$new()

    Analyte$print(...)

    Method join()

    Joins the data of two analytes Performs checks to ensure that the analytes can be joined If the analytes can be joined, the bead_count, analysis_type and units are updated in the current analyte object

    Usage

    Analyte$join(new_analyte)

    Arguments

    new_analyte

    (Analyte)
    The analyte object to be joined with the current analyte object - this is rather a technical inner functionand should rarely be used by the user

    Method clone()

    The objects of this class are cloneable with this method.

    Usage

    Analyte$clone(deep = FALSE)

    Arguments

    deep

    Whether to make a deep clone.

    Examples

    library(PvSTATEM)
etramp <- Analyte$new(id = 73, analyte_name = "Etramp5_ag1", bead_count = 50)
print(etramp)
#> Analyte:  Etramp5_ag1 
#> ID:  73 
#> Bead Count:  50 
#> Analysis Type:
